f importing NativeImageSupport. If I use a dynamic class loading pattern, I might employ Class.forName within SecurityActions for a class that's established at build time. It’s tricky since it can't be open-ended after the build, and I can't catch Unsupported exceptions. I wonder if I need to create a class for instantiation using string overload. Perhaps it could be a nested public static class like `SecurityActionsTest.SampleConstructible`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection and accessibility**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using the `java.lang.reflect.Method` for direct reflection, which seems simple yet requires the `setAccessible(true)` in native contexts. I wonder if the agent metadata includes methods for the class SecurityActions, especially if there's a package-private method. The test might focus more on reflecting the method rather than targeting dynamic access. It's interesting to note that reflection metadata must involve the SecurityActions method and possibly a nested constructor. The agent will keep track of this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZccPkVP5bIEMP3mWX8O5PSwb|fc_0c88092114f0e32c0169f49269d088819e929c14743c2e1d4f", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/main/extracted/org/jboss/shrinkwrap/api/ArchivePath.java"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/main/extracted/org/jboss/shrinkwrap/api/ArchivePath.java\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1180, "output": 1904, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26124, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777635920099, "responseId": "resp_