mporting NativeImageSupport. If I use a dynamic class loading pattern, I might employ Class.forName within SecurityActions for a class that's established at build time. It’s tricky since it can't be open-ended after the build, and I can't catch Unsupported exceptions. I wonder if I need to create a class for instantiation using string overload. Perhaps it could be a nested public static class like `SecurityActionsTest.SampleConstructible`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection and accessibility**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using the `java.lang.reflect.Method` for direct reflection, which seems simple yet requires the `setAccessible(true)` in native contexts. I wonder if the agent metadata includes methods for the class SecurityActions, especially if there's a package-private method. The test might focus more on reflecting the method rather than targeting dynamic access. It's interesting to note that reflection metadata must involve the SecurityActions method and possibly a nested constructor. The agent will keep track of this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZccPkVP5bIEMP3mWX8O5PSwb|fc_0c88092114f0e32c0169f49269d088819e929c14743c2e1d4f", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/main/extracted/org/jboss/shrinkwrap/api/ArchivePath.java"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/main/extracted/org/jboss/shrinkwrap/api/ArchivePath.java\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1180, "output": 1904, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26124, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777635920099, "responseId": "resp_0c88092114f0e32c0169f4925091e8819eb3b5699648041045"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ZccPkVP5bIEMP3mWX8O5PSwb|fc_0c88092114f0e32c0169f49269d088819e929c14743c2e1d4f", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * JBoss, Home of Professional Open Source\n * Copyright 2009, Red Hat Middleware LLC, and individual contributors\n * by the @authors tag. See the copyright.txt in the distribution for a\n * full listing of individual contributors.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage org.jboss.shrinkwrap.api;\n\n/**\n * Represents a target context within an {@link Archive} under which an {@link Node} may be found. All\n * {@link ArchivePath} contexts are absolute (ie. prepended with the '/' character). {@link ArchivePath}s may have\n * parent contexts, unless the path is at the root.\n *\n * @author <a href=\"mailto:andrew.rubinger@jboss.org\">ALR</a>\n */\npublic interface ArchivePath extends Comparable<ArchivePath> {\n\n    /**\n     * Separator character\n     */\n    char SEPARATOR = '/';\n\n    /**\n     * Separator character as a {@link String}\n     */\n    String SEPARATOR_STRING = new Character(SEPARATOR).toString();\n\n    /**\n     * Obtains the context which this {@link ArchivePath} represents\n     *\n     * @return\n     */\n    String get();\n\n    /**\n     * Obtains the parent of this Path, if exists, else null. For instance if the Path is \"/my/path\", the parent will be\n     * \"/my\". Each call will result in a new object reference, though subsequent calls upon the same Path will be equal\n     * by value.\n     *\n     * @return\n     */\n    ArchivePath getParent();\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777635946272}]}
